Abakaliki – The member representing Ikwo/Ezza South Federal Constituency Ebonyi State at the National Assembly, Hon Chinedu Ogah, on Tuesday embarked on humanitarian services to mark his 46th birthday anniversary. Ogah paid unscheduled visits to different groups and institutions across the state where he extended hands of charity to hundreds of less privileged people. The lawmaker commenced his philanthropic journey from a popular place in Abakaliki metropolis beside Pa Ngele Oruta Township Stadium, known as Okporu Oru, where menial job seekers converge daily to look for prospective customers. There, he distributed food items, cash and other gifts to the menial job seekers. Ogah’s second port of call was Old People’s Home, Abakaliki, where he also donated food items, cash and other gifts to them. At Alex Ekwueme Federal Teaching, Abakaliki, Ogah offset the medical bills of indigent patients amounting to millions of naira, and also donated other gift items to the patients. He also visited an orphanage home located at Nsugbe Street Abakaliki, where he also donated food, and other baby items to the home.